  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nWe need a unified component for secure data (password, sync code) input/show.\r\nCurrently `Input.qml` is used for inputing secure data.\r\n\r\n### What's wrong about current solution?\r\n\r\n1. `Input.qml` is copied with many repeating properties over different parts of code, like here:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/1046d6ab4d342c0d558a4102446dcb6a4df126d8/ui/imports/shared/views/PasswordView.qml#L168-L196\r\n\r\n2. It's impossible to bind a button to input's vertical center when it has label \r\n\r\n3. `Input.qml` has fixed invalid bindings inside\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/1046d6ab4d342c0d558a4102446dcb6a4df126d8/ui/imports/shared/controls/Input.qml#L55-L57\r\n\r\n### How about `StatusBaseInput`?\r\n\r\nIt's marked as `TODO` to switch to `StatusBaseInput` when it can work with Passwords\r\n\r\nBut `StatusBaseInput` uses [`TextEdit`](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qml-qtquick-textedit.html) internally, which doesn't have an option of hiding characters.\r\n\r\n### Proposed solution\r\n\r\nCreate a separate `StatusSecureInput` component, which:\r\n- uses [`TextInput`](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qml-qtquick-textinput.html) as internal component\r\n- has a `readOnly` property (synccode can be is read-only, but the characters are black, not grey\r\n- has show/hide button\r\n- has optional copy/paste buttons",
